The paper discusses the application of formal mathematical reasoning to economics, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper specifically mentions game theory, auctions, matching, and financial risk, which are all topics within theoretical computer science (cs.GT). The use of computer-aided reasoning also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The development of a toolbox of formalisations and the study of algorithms and data structures in auctions and matching may also relate to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the organization of events and infrastructure to connect communities suggests a connection to the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.CC).
